---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<BaseLayout>
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-10 text-center">My Trajectory</h2>
    <!-- Aligned Gradient Line -->

    <div
        class="mt-5 h-1.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 via-purple-500 to-pink-500
              rounded-full animate-pulse opacity-80 max-w-4xl mx-auto"
    >
    </div>

    <!-- Applus+ IDIADA -->
    <div
        class="bg-white shadow p-6 rounded-2xl hover:shadow-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto my-8 transition"
    >
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-1">
            Software Engineer ¬∑ Project Manager
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-500 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Applus+ IDIADA</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
            During this period, I led and contributed to several ADAS and
            Autonomous Mobility projects, working across system evaluation,
            computer vision, project management, and tool development.
        </p>

        <!-- Autobrains project -->
        <div class="mb-8">
            <h4 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-lg mb-3">
                Evaluation of a Client's Perception System
            </h4>

            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                I developed and coordinated a complete ADAS EuroNCAP, Regulation
                UN152 and ASEAN NCAP testing program for an AI-based camera
                system, contributing from the earliest client
                interactions‚Äîdefining KPIs, planning validation strategies, and
                aligning expectations‚Äîthrough to implementation and delivery. As
                part of the software team, I helped configure the test
                environment, enabling sensor data capture and automated test
                triggering using technologies such as CAN, C++, Python, and
                Linux.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                To improve communication with the customer, I designed and built
                a reporting tool that visualized test results and analytics
                using React, HTML/CSS, and Python‚Äîsignificantly enhancing how
                insights were presented and increasing the impact of the
                project.
            </p>

            <!-- Single responsive image -->
            <div
                class="mt-8 relative w-full pb-[50%] overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg"
            >
                <Image
                    src="/info/IDIADA's CAVkit.jpg"
                    alt="IDIADA's CAVkit"
                    class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
                    width="1"
                    height="1"
                    loading="eager"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- European projects -->
        <div class="mb-8">
            <h4 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-lg mb-3">
                European Projects
            </h4>

            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                Beyond my technical work, I served as Project Manager for two
                European initiatives in the autonomous mobility domain,
                <a
                    href="https://aithena.eu"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="font-semibold text-indigo-600 hover:underline"
                >
                    AITHENA
                </a>
                and
                <a
                    href="https://aiggregate.eu"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="font-semibold text-indigo-600 hover:underline"
                >
                    AIGGREGATE
                </a>. Within the AITHENA project, I was responsible for leading
                a Work Package, coordinating multiple partners across Europe and
                driving the consortium toward the successful completion of key
                milestones.
            </p>

            <!-- Centered download buttons -->
            <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
                <a
                    href="https://aithena.eu/advancing-tools-and-testing-facilities-in-the-aithena-project-a-look-into-wp4/"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="inline-block bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-indigo-100 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
                >
                    üîó AITHENA WP4 summary
                </a>
            </div>

            <!-- Two responsive images side by side -->
            <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6">
                <!-- Image 1 -->
                <div
                    class="relative w-full sm:w-1/2 pb-[40%] overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg"
                >
                    <Image
                        src="/info/Aithena.jpg"
                        alt="Aithena"
                        class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
                        width="1"
                        height="1"
                    />
                </div>

                <!-- Image 2 -->
                <div
                    class="relative w-full sm:w-1/2 pb-[40%] overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg"
                >
                    <Image
                        src="/info/Aiggregate.jpg"
                        alt="Aiggregate"
                        class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
                        width="1"
                        height="1"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Associate Professor -->
    <div
        class="bg-white shadow p-6 rounded-2xl hover:shadow-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto my-8 transition"
    >
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-1">
            Associate Professor
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-500 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Universitat Rovira i Virgili (URV)
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
            I have been teaching various practical subjects in the
            Telecommunications and Biomedical Engineering degrees, as well as
            their double-degree program at URV. My teaching portfolio includes:
        </p>

        <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4 text-justify"
        >
            <li>
                <strong>Digital Electronics:</strong> Students worked with Xilinx
                FPGA boards, programming logic in VHDL, and developed a multi-functional
                clock project.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong
                    >Technologies for Sensor Networks, IoT, and Smart Cities:</strong
                > Practical exercises included Arduino UNO applications with WiFi/Zigbee,
                uploading sensor data to ThinkSpeak, and using Silicon Labs EFR32
                modules programmed in C (Simplicity Studio IDE) with Zigbee connectivity.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Digital Communications:</strong> Students learned digital
                modulation techniques (M-PSK, M-QAM, etc.) and error calculation
                metrics, simulating them in Matlab.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Communications Fundamentals:</strong> Covers analog and digital
                communication concepts (FFT, AM, FM, etc.) with practical exercises.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Centered button for professor courses -->
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
            <a
                href="https://www.urv.cat/html/grupsrecerca/investigadors/docencia-I79429.php"
                target="_blank"
                class="inline-block bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-indigo-100 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
            >
                üéì View Courses at URV
            </a>
        </div>

        <div
            class="relative w-full pb-[59%] overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg mt-10 gap-6"
        >
            <Image
                src="/info/Associate_professor.jpg"
                alt="Associate professor"
                class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
                width="1"
                height="1"
            />
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Programming Trainer -->
    <div
        class="bg-white shadow p-6 rounded-2xl hover:shadow-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto my-8 transition"
    >
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-1">
            Programming Trainer
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-500 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Acad√®mia Gaud√≠</p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
            I have been developing and teaching various programming courses,
            primarily focused on Python. My teaching portfolio includes:
        </p>

        <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4 text-justify"
        >
            <li>
                <strong>Introduction to Python:</strong> A 6-hour course covering
                the fundamentals of Python programming, including data types and
                operators, data structures, control flow, functions, modules and
                libraries, file handling, error handling, and script execution.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Advanced Python:</strong> A 6-hour course focusing on advanced
                Python workflows and libraries, including NumPy, Pandas DataFrames,
                plotting with Matplotlib and Plotly, and machine learning with scikit-learn,
                PyTorch, and TensorFlow.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Robot Programming for Kids:</strong> A 3-hour introductory
                course for children to explore programming using Mbot and the Makeblock
                framework.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Centered button for Reel's teaching -->
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
            <a
                href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/C57xNrxts60/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA=="
                target="_blank"
                class="inline-block bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-indigo-100 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
            >
                üé• Watch Teaching Reel
            </a>
        </div>

        <div
            class="relative w-full pb-[59%] overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg mt-10 gap-6"
        >
            <Image
                src="/info/Python_course.jpg"
                alt="Python course"
                class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
                width="1"
                height="1"
            />
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- NEPHOS Lab -->
    <div
        class="bg-white shadow p-6 rounded-2xl hover:shadow-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto my-8 transition"
    >
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-1">R&D Engineer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-500 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            NEPHOS Lab ¬∑ Universitat Rovira i Virgili (URV)
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
            During my time at the NEPHOS Lab, I focused on analyzing commercial
            radar systems and developing real-world applications. My work
            centered on two main automotive projects working with a Texas
            Instruments Radar:
        </p>

        <!-- Occupancy Detection System -->
        <div class="mb-8">
            <h4 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-lg mb-3">
                Occupancy Detection System
            </h4>

            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                I developed a radar-based occupancy detection system for the
                interior of vehicles, leveraging Texas Instruments radar
                technology.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                This project formed the thesis of my Final Telecommunications
                degree and was recognized with the
                <a
                    href="https://acarmitt.es/index.php/noticias/117-alto-nivel-demostrado-en-esta-xv-premios-futuro-de-las-telecomunicaciones"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="font-semibold text-indigo-600 hover:underline"
                >
                    "Future of Telecommunications" Award
                </a>
                by the Official College of Telecommunication Engineers (COITT) in
                the category of Telecommunications Systems Engineering.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                The results were also published in the <em
                    >IEEE Sensors Journal</em
                > as the paper <em
                    >‚ÄúVehicle Occupancy Detector Based on FMCW mm-Wave Radar at
                    77 GHz‚Äù</em
                >
            </p>

            <!-- Centered download buttons -->
            <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
                <a
                    href="/info/IEEESensors_77GHz.pdf"
                    download
                    class="bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-indigo-100 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
                >
                    üìÑ Paper (PDF)
                </a>
                <a
                    href="/info/MemoriaTFG_NilMunteGuerrero.pdf"
                    class="inline-block bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-indigo-100 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
                    download
                >
                    üéì Final Thesis Project (PDF)
                </a>
                <a
                    href="https://github.com/nil-munte/Radar_Texas_AWR1642/tree/main/01-Matlab/01-ProjecteCotxe"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="inline-block bg-gray-800 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-gray-700 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
                >
                    üíª View Project (GitHub)
                </a>
            </div>

            <!-- Responsive YouTube video -->
            <div
                class="relative w-full pb-[56.25%] overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg mt-6"
            >
                <iframe
                    class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full"
                    src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6adK5tNakV8"
                    title="Occupancy Detection Project Video"
                    loading="lazy"
                    allowfullscreen
                >
                </iframe>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Hand-Gesture Detection System -->
        <div class="mb-8">
            <h4 class="text-gray-700 font-semibold text-lg mb-2">
                Hand-Gesture Detection System
            </h4>

            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed text-justify">
                Designed and implemented a hand-gesture recognition system using
                Matlab and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). The results of
                this project were published under the title
                <em
                    >‚ÄúIn-Vehicle Monitoring Based on a Low-Cost mm-Wave Radar at
                    60 GHz‚Äù</em
                >
                at the <em>IEEE IMOC 2023 conference. </em>

                <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
                    <a
                        href="/info/IEEE_IMOC2023_60GHz_v3short.pdf"
                        class="inline-block bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-indigo-100 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
                        download
                    >
                        üìÑ Paper (PDF)
                    </a>
                    <a
                        href="https://github.com/nil-munte/Radar_Texas_AWR1642/tree/main/01-Matlab/02-ProjecteGestos"
                        target="_blank"
                        class="inline-block bg-gray-800 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-gray-700 hover:-translate-y-0.5 active:translate-y-0 transition-all"
                    >
                        üíª View Project (GitHub)
                    </a>
                </div>

                <!-- Embedded Video -->
                <div
                    class="relative w-full pb-[56.25%] overflow-hidden rounded-lg shadow-lg mt-4"
                >
                    <iframe
                        class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full"
                        src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/TX15-d1m26U"
                        title="Example Project Video"
                        loading="lazy"
                        allowfullscreen
                    >
                    </iframe>
                </div>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
